inux",[324,320],"https://image2url.com/r2/default/images/1772468211054-abb465e3-17e6-4220-b412-63a35671e73b.png","https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=KratosGado.nasm-compiler-linux",{},{"icon":116},"/projects/nasm-compiler-for-linux",{"title":263,"description":321},"nasm-compiler-for-linux",[301,307,313],"projects/nasm-compiler-for-linux","okvhZFVqpK0Wp4Km0pKNMtTZFCu1rzFOQP16pOCJrwA",{"id":335,"title":336,"body":337,"coverImage":381,"description":382,"extension":105,"github":383,"images":384,"liveUrl":97,"meta":385,"navigation":386,"path":387,"rank":98,"seo":388,"slug":389,"stack":390,"stem":391,"__hash__":392},"projects/projects/pseudo-code-interpreter.md","Pseudo Code Interpreter",{"type":22,"value":338,"toc":376},[339,341,344,346,366,368],[25,340,28],{"id":27},[30,342,343],{},"Pseudo Code Interpreter is a Rust-based tool that interprets and executes pseudo code files passed as command-line arguments. It allows developers to test their algorithms written in pseudo code.",[25,345,36],{"id":35},[38,347,348,354,360],{},[41,349,350,353],{},[44,351,352],{},"Command-Line Interface",": Run pseudo code files from the terminal.",[41,355,356,359],{},[44,357,358],{},"Interpretation",": Executes pseudo code syntax.",[41,361,362,365],{},[44,363,364],{},"Error Handling",": Provides feedback on invalid syntax.",[25,367,63],{"id":62},[38,369,370],{},[41,371,372,375],{},[44,373,374],{},"Rust",": A systems programming language that runs blazingly fast, prevents segfaults, and guarantees thread safety.",{"title":97,"searchDepth":98,"depth":98,"links":377},[378,379,380],{"id":27,"depth":98,"text":28},{"id":35,"depth":98,"text":36},{"id":62,"depth":98,"text":63},"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/d/16349CIC6DYXDHTwt75gVh1bworLk95VZ","A pseudo code interpreter written in rust that interprets pseudocode file passed to it as cli argument.","https://github.com/Kratosgado/pseudo_interpreter",[],{},{"icon":116},"/projects/pseudo-code-interpreter",{"title":336,"description":382},"pseudo-code-interpreter",[374],"projects/pseudo-code-interpreter","3OvJwE5V_aJ7DZ0Jdn5-jqt5hYmsae-y8gKG1vLvUPw",{"id":394,"title":395,"body":396,"coverImage":381,"description":475,"extension":105,"github":476,"images":477,"liveUrl":479,"meta":480,"navigation":481,"path":482,"rank":98,"seo":483,"slug":484,"stack":485,"stem":486,"__hash__":487},"projects/projects/pseudo-runner.md","Pseudo Runner",{"type":22,"value":397,"toc":469},[398,400,403,405,431,435,443,447],[25,399,28],{"id":27},[30,401,402],{},"Pseudo Runner is a VS Code extension that allows you to write and execute pseudo code directly within the editor. It provides syntax highlighting, code execution, and output display all in one place.",[25,404,36],{"id":35},[38,406,407,413,419,425],{},[41,408,409,412],{},[44,410,411],{},"Syntax Highlighting",": Full pseudo code syntax support",[41,414,415,418],{},[44,416,417],{},"In-Editor Execution",": Run your pseudo code without leaving VS Code",[41,420,421,424],{},[44,422,423],{},"Output Panel",": See execution results in a dedicated output panel",[41,426,427,430],{},[44,428,429],{},"Error Reporting",": Clear error messages with line numbers",[25,432,434],{"id":433},"how-it-works","How It Works",[30,436,437,438,442],{},"The extension registers a custom language mode for ",[439,440,441],"code",{},".pseudo"," files and provides a built-in interpreter that parses and executes the code. Results are displayed in the VS Code output panel.",[25,444,446],{"id":445},"getting-started","Getting Started",[448,449,450,453,459,462],"ol",{},[41,451,452],{},"Install the extension from the VS Code Marketplace",[41,454,455,456,458],{},"Create a new file with the ",[439,457,441],{}," extension",[41,460,461],{},"Write your pseudo code",[41,463,464,465,468],{},"Press ",[439,466,467],{},"Ctrl+Shift+P"," and run \"Pseudo Runner: Execute\"",{"title":97,"searchDepth":98,"depth":98,"links":470},[471,472,473,474],{"id":27,"depth":98,"text":28},{"id":35,"depth":98,"text":36},{"id":433,"dept